Well, as I said, these determinations are up to the house style.<p>I prefer that blocks of code hold together -- think of them as paragraphs.  Spacing each sentence of a paragraph out is similarly confusing.  But as you say, YMMV.<p>I find
  return is_valid(result) ? result : ERR_CODE;
common and clear, but perhaps you don&#x27;t.<p>I do think that any style guide should forbid while and do..while simply because for has become by far the looping construct of choice in C.<p>In all cases the point should be correctness and clarity, not showing off that you use unusual language features.
